website_summaries.verdict: Tasty, beautiful dry food is the perfect way to spoil your dog in a healthy way.
pros: Kibble is full of quality, healthy ingredients that you can actually see
Taste and smell are appetizing to even the pickiest of eaters
Small 3.75-pound bag is the perfect size to sample
Free of soy, wheat, and gluten
cons: Dried carrots and peas are quite hard and may be difficult to chew for some

customer_reviews.title: His breath is so much better also. He has a lot of energy and ...
customer_reviews.text: We recently adopted a foster dog. He was being fed Pedigree by the foster mom (she was fostering several dogs, so I understand buying the cheaper dog food). I bought a small bag of Pedigree and mixed it with this food so our puppy would ease into it. I guess I we had nothing to worry about. He loves this food. He is part Shepherd and part Black Mouth Cur. His breath is so much better also. He has a lot of energy and is a great puppy too. I feel better feeding him healthier food without all the byproducts and junk in it. I have this on Subscribe & Save since he loves it so much.
customer_reviews.author: Jen Nelson from Texas

customer_reviews.title: BEST DOG FOOD ON THE MARKET! This is the only food I will ever buy again!
customer_reviews.text: Best product out there! I do not worry that my dogs aren't getting the proper nutrition; the Rachel Ray dog food is the best. My dogs absolutely love it! It has yummy chunks of fruit and vegetables which the dogs pick out to eat first. No fillers and I can tell my dogs are thoroughly satisfied. Plus a big plus is there isn't a lot of waste to clean up as the dogs absorb the good nutrition. I am totally impressed with Rachel's line of dog foods. We have tried several - love them all - but I do like this one the best, and so do my furry little kids!
customer_reviews.author: B. Anderson

customer_reviews.title: Our dogs ❤ Nutrish DISH
customer_reviews.text: Our dogs love Nutrish Dish. Our fox terrier has all kinds of allergy issues but this food Works for her, and we are thrilled. The dogs love what goes into Nutrish, and we love what is NOT added: (no corn, wheat, soy, gluten, artificial preservatives or colors, And no meat by-products. ) Real meat and veggies...Wonderful product. Thank you, Rachael.
customer_reviews.author: josie

customer_reviews.title: Great dog good, price...not so much
customer_reviews.text: I can't keep this food in my either of my dogs bowls. They love it. They love the treats too. BIG SCORE for me. Price is outrageous. Most of the time it is double the price of moderately priced dog food, but I feel it is much healthier for them than the other brands I was using, so I'm gonna bit the bullet for the love of my fur buddies..
customer_reviews.author: KristySunshine

customer_reviews.title: Our dog loves this food!
customer_reviews.text: Our dog is fairly picky when it comes to food. We have found that she likes the Rachel Ray line of products, and that is now our go to food for her. When we tried DISH instead of the Zero-grain, she was so excited to eat, every time we fed her! She would get like this with certain foods, but the new would wear off and she wasn't always as excited. With DISH, she runs to her bowl and eats her food as soon as it is served! I like that it is a well balanced meal for her.
customer_reviews.author: Chouser

customer_reviews.title: Not the same as the grocery store version
customer_reviews.text: Dogs snub until hungry. In this bag, all of the food pellets look the same minus subtle coloring differences. Grocery store bags have peices that are shaped and colored like peas, carrots etc. My dogs eat it up. However, my dogs only eat this version if I mix it with actual meat and veggies. Glad we finally ran out so I can go back to the grocery store version.
customer_reviews.author: AmazonShopper

customer_reviews.title: Our Yorkies love this food more than the super-premium brands!
customer_reviews.text: Our yorkies love this food and they're finicky eaters. We rotate their food with DISH Chicken & Brown Rice, DISH Beef & Brown Rice, Royal Canin Yorkie (28), Royal Canin Puppy (33) and Simply Nourish mini chicken & brown rice. They like both DISH flavors, the DISH Beef & Brown Rice the best. (our small male loves the carrots and potatoes). The pieces are mini-sized, but the meat chunks are a bit large, so we break them up in the bowl. Only a little over $40 for a 23-pound bag from Amazon makes the cost per pound about half as much as the other brands we purchase.
customer_reviews.author: Mitchel Martin

customer_reviews.title: Glad we tried this
customer_reviews.text: My Boston has been on & off Blue & Wellness since we adopted him 3 years ago. After a couple of weeks he gets tired of his food, so we been trying to find something he'll like. So we decided to try Nutrish. He loves it. And after 3 weeks, he still eating it. He eats all the fruits & veggies & loves digging for the chicken pieces (always see pieces of chicken when pouring food).
customer_reviews.author: Fitz Roy

customer_reviews.title: Good quality but not my dogs favorite
customer_reviews.text: We've used Rachael Ray dog food for nearly 2 years and been very happy. We typically use Just 6, but I was travelling and wanted to have a smaller bag delivered to my destination ahead of our arrival but the Just 6 was not available in a smaller size. My 18lb silky terrier ate the food and seemed satisfied, however, she didn't like the dried carrots and would leave them on the floor outside her bowl. She also seemed to only like the dried peas some of the time. Visually, the food made me feel good as a pet parent as it was clearly dried pieces of "real" food but I don't think my dog was a big fan.
customer_reviews.author: Erin V

customer_reviews.title: World's pickiest dog's approved
customer_reviews.text: I have two yorkies and they are world's pickiest dogs. I have spent so much money trying to find food that they both will like and eat that doesn't upset one or both of their stomachs. I was at a friend's house a my dogs would not stop eating the dog food she had, so I k we I had to buy them some. The one downside is, my younger guy spits the peas out so I find them all over my kitchen floor.
customer_reviews.author: Lindsay

customer_reviews.title: My pup was apparently allergic
customer_reviews.text: Bought this as a "hold over" when our regular food ran out - mistake. We had to throw away half the bag because our golden mix was apparently highly allergic. Almost immediately she was itching like mad, 24/7. She lost a ton of hair and became so sensitive that if you touched her back she flinched. We figured it out after about 3 weeks and switched her back to her regular food - after 2 weeks she's back to normal. No idea what it was, hopefully just a fluke.
customer_reviews.author: NotMilk

customer_reviews.title: Affordable Quality Food
customer_reviews.text: My dogs love this dry dog food. I had been purchasing another one of her dry foods that is cheaper, but I prefer this one. It has freeze dried carrots, peas, and meat in it. I feel like it’s a very healthy dog food. I have tried other well rated expensive dry foods (Ulta and blue) but my dogs prefer this one, and the price is much more affordable.
customer_reviews.author: Mama C

customer_reviews.title: Will not buy again as it made our dogs sick
customer_reviews.text: With the weather we’ve had here in the great plains we always like to keep extra dog and cat food on hand and usually we have no problem with Rachel Ray’s dog food; however, this time was the exception. We opened one of the two bags that we ordered in January 2019 on March 20, 2019 and all three of our dogs got sick. They had nothing else other than this bag of Rachel Ray Beef Dish dog food and their water. I was not happy and had three sick dogs for two days. I will not buy this ever again. Very disappointed as we had been RR dog food users since it came out.
customer_reviews.author: KetIsTheName

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love it!
customer_reviews.text: My two Miniature Schnauzers really like this food. They eat a stress formula due to their tendency to get overly excited and end up with sick stomachs. But, they are not crazy about that food. I looked for something that I could mix with that food, and this absolutely does the trick. Much better than mixing in a wet food or adding some chicken or beef broth. And it's healthier than those options.
customer_reviews.author: CarolTop Contributor: Coloring

customer_reviews.title: The amount of veg. is not the same as ...
customer_reviews.text: The amount of veg. is not the same as it look on the picture and commercial. There is a lot less mixed in than shown on picture . This is disappointing because I normally add veg to his dog food so with this food I didn't think that I would have to add more. Plus there is no zipper on the bag to keep the dog food fresh
customer_reviews.author: Laura ac

customer_reviews.title: Bad ingredients
customer_reviews.text: First, my dogs do like this dog food. But the ingredients are not healthy and the sourcing is from areas of the world I would not want for my dogs’ food. I’ve been hoping they would revamp their formulas to remove potatoes, peas, and all legumes in light of the dog health scare that’s now been identified by the FDA and the USDA from using those ingredients, causing serious medical conditions in dogs. This brand was on the list published by the FDA of foods with reported serious health issues in dogs who ate it.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: NO MORE GAS!
customer_reviews.text: My 7yr old Maltese and 2yr old Pitadot are gas free! I started feeding them Rachael Ray's Nutrish dry foods and treats over a year ago. No more gas now! Before, I fed them Wild or Blue Buffalo. They passed gas so badly, there was little breathable air left in the room once they started passing gas. Thanks Rachael for coming up with a food that is healthy for my boys and reduces or rids them of daily flatulence problems! Oh, they love it too.🐶🐶
customer_reviews.author: Ell Coulb

customer_reviews.title: Dogs love it!
customer_reviews.text: This is a great value size and price for this bag of food! My Miniature Pinschers Love it and it is a Great quality food! It has small pieces of dried vegetables all throughout the bag and the pieces are small for my dogs to chew! The bag is made of a plastic material not paper cardboard like other brands! I have tried different flavors of Rachel Ray and my dogs have loved every one of them! Definitely recommend!
customer_reviews.author: Shuck

customer_reviews.title: Doesn’t give my dog seizures like most kibble  does
customer_reviews.text: I have a dog that gets seizures from most kibble. I make homemade food for them as a result. However ,this brand does not affect her negatively! I keep it in the bowl to supplement them if I run out of homemade food. They don’t gobble it up but will eat it if nothing else is available. Truth be told, all dry dog food in my opinion is gross and can’t be great for our pets but this one seems to be decent enough and if they aren’t throwing it up or having seizures , it maybe it has less of the bad stuff the the rest of them
customer_reviews.author: Taylor

customer_reviews.title: Best darn food for my Labradoodle!
customer_reviews.text: While this dog food is on the upper side in cost it's well worth it. My dog gets bored with other dog food, NOT with Rachel Ray's. It has a variety of size and types of kibbles mixed in with veggies. He does on occasion pick out the peas band leave around his dish. It's easy to give five stars and a very positive review!
customer_reviews.author: Electric Z

customer_reviews.title: DO NOT FEED THIS TO YOUR DOG!!!
customer_reviews.text: I ordered this but will not be feeding this to my Dog! My Son has spent 1,400.00 at the vet because his Dog ate this food. She also came home from the vet in 6 different medications.She is still sick and we don't know if she will make it. The Vet said specifically the food has caused her sickness. My Dogs stomach was upset and throwing up, I spent 178.00 and she is on stomach medication now. I found out that a Family members dog passed away eating this food. She has the records from her vet and had also been in contact with the company. Please do NOT feed this to your dog!!!
customer_reviews.author: Pscott65

customer_reviews.title: but it does not look like that when you get it
customer_reviews.text: The picture you see in the commercial about this food is very deceptive. It shows a lot of veggies in with the food, but it does not look like that when you get it. There are some veggies in it just not as much as advertised. My dog does like it and I think it is a good product. I will continue using it, but had to give it a 3 star review for the reasons listed.
customer_reviews.author: D. Maxey

customer_reviews.title: so maybe I don't love it, but the dog sure does
customer_reviews.text: Okay....so maybe I don't love it, but the dog sure does. It doesn't quite look as good as it does on the bag, but you can tell right away when you pour it out, it's not your typical dog food. And our dog sure knew it as well. She went from "I'll eat that when I get around to it" to "Get outta my way!" I'm not a nutritionist, but it certainly looks healthier than brown chunks of unidentifiable kibble.
customer_reviews.author: Darrel Weston

customer_reviews.title: My dogs loved it!
customer_reviews.text: Dogs loved it and their tummies didn't get bloated. It was the one food I found that didn't have allergens for my poodle. Sadly to say, I lost her last summer due to congestive heart failure. NOTHING to do with the dog food. She actually did better after I found out she had allergies. The CHF wasn't found soon enough in my humble opinion, her Chongqing and breathing problems were diagnosed as "allergies" Unfortunately, she had both. From her diagnosis, she lived 4 months. She defied all, and played & loved hard to the very end. I soaked the food in chicken broth which i mostly homemade to get them to drink more water and soften the food.
customer_reviews.author: Tah

customer_reviews.title: A little pricey but worth it!
customer_reviews.text: My Shih Tzu loves this food! More so than other food that I have tried. She enjoys her dinner time, and jumps right in and eats! You can see the vegetables in the food, and in her poop too, lol. Her stool is better formed with this food than with other food. No smelly farts! That’s a big plus! Together we love this food, other than the price of $2.00 a pound this food is great.
customer_reviews.author: Lori From Michigan

customer_reviews.title: My dog is a picky eater, definitely not the ...
customer_reviews.text: My dog is a picky eater, definitely not the dog who gobbles up all the food in sight. It can sometimes take her two days to finish her bowl of food, but not this food, she will eat it all up!
customer_reviews.author: CdS_OlS_SkS

customer_reviews.title: Carrots?
customer_reviews.text: Well, this is somewhat amusing to watch our two dogs (Husky and German Shepard) eat this. They very carefully pick out the dried carrot pieces and spit them onto the floor while looking at me with a "WTF" look in their eyes. Otherwise, they do seem to enjoy this but I will switch back to a non-veggie mix so I can stop cleaning up soggy carrot pieces.
customer_reviews.author: Live Free

customer_reviews.title: Easier for seniors to eat and digest
customer_reviews.text: We switched to this from another Nutrish type because my senior dogs needed something a little easier to eat and digest. Fewer teeth, aging body and all. We no longer have to wet their food and they seem happy with it. It really is more expensive than other foods though.
customer_reviews.author: MomOf3Crazies

customer_reviews.title: Wanted to try something new for a puppy  :-(
customer_reviews.text: I have to soak this food in order for my 5 month old mini poodle to eat. He is teething and noticed that the peas are so hard, they do not soften. May have been over dried in processing. Still hard at a rock after 10 min soak time. Poor guy loves peas. So I opened a can of peas and remove this ones in this dry food. This food is new to us and probably will switch to Hills Science diet.
customer_reviews.author: Carolyn Ortagus

customer_reviews.title: Not enough quality protein
customer_reviews.text: No My rescues lose hair in patches when I try a food that is not balanced. Please help. I cook protein for them and give them this dog food. I've tried sooooo many brand. The fact is, they're not sufficient with protein. At least not what our dogs can absorb.
customer_reviews.author: Amelie

customer_reviews.title: No Preservatives
customer_reviews.text: Dry or mixed with Peak my dogs love it, Shar-peis are prone to hair loss, skins troubles, I've tried others and she eventually loses all of her hair when I try something else. I will never switch to anything else, no upset stomach, no hair loss, bright eyes, Rachel Ray brand clearly cares about what my dog is eating and what she attaches her name to, it's more, yeah, but it's worth it.
customer_reviews.author: Kitena Suttles

customer_reviews.title: My dogs liked it, until we got one bad bag over a year
customer_reviews.text: My two cookapoo's seemed to like it, except for the peas, they would like them behind in the living room and in their dish. We have never had an issue until our last order, the bag had a few clumps of mold and dog food. I am not sure if it related to storage or manufacture. Amazon gave us a refund, and have decided to try another brand without the peas the boys don't like. We still use the smoochies, they love those and it is more affordable that greenies.
customer_reviews.author: Kevin M.

customer_reviews.title: he gets excited for each meal and is sad when his food gets changed up
customer_reviews.text: My friend's shiba inu loves this dog food, except for the peas. He will individually and painstakingly pick each pea out of his bowl and set them aside. But despite the fact that he hates the peas, he gets excited for each meal and is sad when his food gets changed up. My maltipoo however, loves the peas and everything else, so she ends up cleaning his mess, so it all works out! My friend and I are always looking for dog food with quality ingredients for a good price and this fits the bill! Rachel Ray dog food has been a hit for these puppers.
customer_reviews.author: Sayurichan

customer_reviews.title: Yummy & Healthy For Your Doggies!
customer_reviews.text: I have two growing dogs both over a year old and this food is their absolute favorite! Inside of the food is chunks of veggies and fruits and also has rice and beef kibbles. Rachel Ray is the best brand for dog food. For my two dogs I try to mix it up but i always stick to the same brand. They also have chicken flavor. Definitely would recommend from my doggies to yours!
customer_reviews.author: Justin

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love it!
customer_reviews.text: I have 2 poodle mixes who were rather picky (about their dog food anyways), they have been eating this for around 2 years now and eat it all, everytime! I usually switch between the chicken and beef flavors for them. I couldn't always find the larger bag nearby... so having it available here, is the best bang for my buck... double bonus for not having to lug the bag around and supporting a great cause! Funny side note, my dogs some how sift the peas out?!!... I vacuum twice a day because of it, stepping on those peas barefoot is no joke!
customer_reviews.author: LA

customer_reviews.title: Best dog food ever!
customer_reviews.text: Best dog food on the market. I originally tried it because of a coupon I had. Too bad some stores don't stock enough of it. My dog is a self regulating eater and when we mix this with another grain free dog food for our black lab, she is the happiest dog on the block! It has pieces of dehydrated peas, carrots and chicken that our princess thinks are treats. The perfect mix is great on her stomach too, making yard pick up a breeze! Happy dog, happy mom!
customer_reviews.author: sportygirl

customer_reviews.title: I love it, BTD
customer_reviews.text: Bestest and most yummiest dog food ever! One time, my owner couldn’t find this so she purchased a lesser brand with a similar photo. When she poured it in my bowl, I instantly knew it wasn’t Rachael Ray’s Dish!!!! I became distraught and ended up going to bed hungry. My people made it right the very next day, and thanks to Amazon, I’ll never run out again. It’s one Alexa command away. Sincerely, Beasley the Dog
customer_reviews.author: Travis

customer_reviews.title: my dog doesn't like the dried carrots so good
customer_reviews.text: Having to mix this with other food to try to get him use to it.....my dog doesn't like the dried carrots so good.....but he picked them out not to eat., and eats the rest
customer_reviews.author: lovada vaughn

customer_reviews.title: No veggies/fruit
customer_reviews.text: I have bought Rachel ray dish wild rice chicken with veggies and fruit for a couple years and my dogs love it. But this bag was not acceptable. There was no veggies or fruit. Just dog fruit. They didn’t like it. I’m going to start buying royal canin from PetSmart. The vet said it much better for my dogs.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: great for my finicky pup
customer_reviews.text: I've tried almost all of the Nutrish variants, and my finicky chihuahua-minpin mix tends to like all of them more than other brands I've tried, but Dish is his new favorite. Perhaps it's the small kibble or the dried bits of fruits and vegetables, or just the taste, but he loves it!
customer_reviews.author: Aaron Fox

customer_reviews.title: Dogs. Not eating
customer_reviews.text: My two Huskies did not like this food at all, the ingredients from what is seen were all natural vegetables , peas , carrots , thought they would enjoy , but to my surprise NO! I don’t think there was anything wrong with food , went back to Purina brand , they love that- more value for your buck.
customer_reviews.author: Carol R.

customer_reviews.title: NOT for small breed adult
customer_reviews.text: This product is not good for small breed dogs. My dog had the hardest time to eat it. A good portion ended on the floor (my dog never has food on the floor when eating). In addition, it contains grains which immediately constipated the dog. My poor baby...he is pooping pebbles. :( throwing away the bag and going to something else.
customer_reviews.author: alia

customer_reviews.title: No longer the quality from years past.
customer_reviews.text: My dogs loved this for several years. Wouldn't eat anything else. In the past year both refuse to touch it. The oldest one (a mini schnauzer) would go without food rather than eat Dish. In the past, it was the only dog food he WOULD eat. I started asking questions and found out that Rachel Ray no longer makes this dog food. She sold her dog food brand (for $2 billion) to J.M. Smucker Company in 2018. Which why the quality has fallen.
customer_reviews.author: Kathy Cunningham

customer_reviews.title: NUTRISH DIsh , my dog is not a fan
customer_reviews.text: My 4yo poodle mix will normally eat anything. However he will not eat this Dish brand until he has to. I will say he gobbles up the large pieces but they are few and far between. I will have to go back to regular Nutrish.
customer_reviews.author: KaeBoo

customer_reviews.title: She loves it!
customer_reviews.text: I give my dog some chicken Nutrish yesterday for the first time. She ate it all, which rarely happens. Today, I tried to switch back to her old food, but she wouldn't eat it. I had to dump it and give her back the Nutrish. My only complaint is that the actual product doesn't have as much vegetables as in the commercials.
customer_reviews.author: Cas Alex

customer_reviews.title: Quality but pricey
customer_reviews.text: Dogs love this. But I think it’s a bit overpriced. But good ingredients and never had an issue with the product being opened or stale, etc. my dogs love the peas and carrots, even my finicky eater eats this. My dogs all eat it, two are just very slow, the other 2 eat it without hesitating.
customer_reviews.author: AJ is Peachy

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: My small breed maltipoo loved this food even though the pieces are too big. I'm rewriting my review as I realized his dog food stains my guys white hair around his mouth. I've tried washing it off but he has a brown red tint that won't go away, He likes the food but would not recommend if your dog has white hair. Since I can't return, I will be send it to the animal shelter.
customer_reviews.author: Redhead

customer_reviews.title: Received a trial package of this and my dog loved it; however
customer_reviews.text: Received a trial package of this and my dog loved it; however, when I ordered this, there were virtually no vegetables in the mix, only dry food. The vegetables were what my dog loved. Will not order again.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Healthy for my dog...
customer_reviews.text: My dogs only preferred meal has real veggies /meat in with no grain morsels. My Roxi loves this food, i do top it with little broken apart dehydrated chicken pieces. And mix in a half container of Cesars Home Delight choices. My daughters dog loves to steal my Roxi's left overs. Her dog is on some food highly recommended by their breeder.
customer_reviews.author: crafty reader

customer_reviews.title: Allergic reactions suddenly
customer_reviews.text: I have fed this to my dog since she was able to eat adult dog food. At 4 years old my pup just started experience allergies to this food developing stomach complications, dry skin and irritated skin allergies. This started happening as soon as I started ordering from Amazon so it's either a different ingredient mix sent from the warehouse or something along the lines. I would not recommend feeding to your dog, if you do, buy from the grocery store and at least beware of the overall quality of this product.
customer_reviews.author: Minitey

customer_reviews.title: My Dog Loves This Food!
customer_reviews.text: I bought this food because I can actually see what is in it - the peas and carrots are identifiable, and there are chunks of meatiness in addition to the kibbles. I was happily surprised when my dog agreed with my choice! My dog is a picky eater and would rather go hungry than eat something she doesn't like.
customer_reviews.author: lballas

customer_reviews.title: BELLA APPROVES
customer_reviews.text: Bella Loves this brand, She tends to pick out the vegetable 1st then works her way around everything else. I love that the ingredients are more natural then some specially since my baby girl gets allergies from anything and is super sensitive to what she can eat with out upsetting her tummy.
customer_reviews.author: Solange

customer_reviews.title: ... bag of this dog food and it looked nothing like what she advertises on tv
customer_reviews.text: Bought a bag of this dog food and it looked nothing like what she advertises on tv. Pieces of dried fruit and veggies were so tiny you really had to search for them.
customer_reviews.author: scott h bailey

customer_reviews.title: Dog loves it!
customer_reviews.text: What more can I say? My dog loves it. More than his usual, which I didn't buy because its twice the price I usually pay in the store. The ratings for this aren't very high in the veterinary world, but hey....like I said, the dog loves it.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great kibble
customer_reviews.text: Our Dobe is picky but the Beef with Brown Rice is her fav. A little warm water added and it really smells great! It not as expensive as other kibble but wish it were a bit less. We liked that it has a high protein content.
customer_reviews.author: parachutegirl

customer_reviews.title: My dog will not eat it.
customer_reviews.text: My dog a 100 lb Pit mix will not eat this food, normally she will eat anything. I mixed with her regular food, but that did not help, she would eat some but not all of it, which ie unusual for her.
customer_reviews.author: Bart W. Lewis

customer_reviews.title: Awesome
customer_reviews.text: Very good pet food. My Sugar loves it so much except she obviously is not fond of carrots, she picks them out of the bowl and quickly deposits them on the kitchen floor. We all have our druthers I guess. It really is all natural and if you want to keep a healthy pet I highly recommend this food.
customer_reviews.author: Teresa H.

customer_reviews.title: Don't buy from Big Box seller!
customer_reviews.text: My dog is a picky eater. He loves this food. But dont order from big box seller. I live in Iowa. They sent my order to new york. I have never lived in new york. My address is in the midwest!
customer_reviews.author: Lorali

customer_reviews.title: My frenchies fav.
customer_reviews.text: We have tried a few brands and this one is the best for the price. Our dog loves the real veggies in the food. Comforts me to see her eat something other then just brown pebbles. lol
customer_reviews.author: Crystal

customer_reviews.title: Not what was expected...
customer_reviews.text: Expected the little dried meat pieces to be bigger. They are 1/8” thick by 1/4” little squares. There are very few veggies or meat pieces in the bag. No better than regular dog food.
customer_reviews.author: K. Gordon

customer_reviews.title: A treat in itself!
customer_reviews.text: My dogs don't get excited for regular food, only if we add a treat like bacon grease. But this... they come running! It is a treat all on its own to them. They never got this excited for Blue Buffalo. Plus, BB was making one of my dogs struggle with movements. Dish keeps both of them regular.
customer_reviews.author: IResearchStuff

customer_reviews.title: My GSD wasn't real excited about this dog food
customer_reviews.text: Dog initially took a couple of bites and then walked away. Had to mix with hamburger or something else "organic" and then she would eat it. Kibble is pretty small, and would prefer larger pieces suitable for a large dog like a GSD. I'll look for alternative dry food next time around.
customer_reviews.author: GrayslakeTop Contributor: Pets

customer_reviews.title: Doggy likes it
customer_reviews.text: I do use about 3 different brands I buy for my dog and I mix them up in a big container. I like to give her a good high quality variety to ensure she gets the right nutrients

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love the dries veggies
